# macOS Developer ID signing + notarization credentials.
#
# Setup:
#   cp .env.signing.example .env.signing
#   # fill in the values below (never commit .env.signing)
#
# Build:
#   just sign
#   # or: just sign-release-desktop / ./scripts/tauri-sign-release.sh
#
# Full guide: docs/DEVELOPMENT.md → "macOS signed release"

# Optional — auto-detected from keychain if only one Developer ID Application exists.
# APPLE_SIGNING_IDENTITY="Developer ID Application: Your Name (TEAMID)"

# Apple ID notarization (create an app-specific password at appleid.apple.com)
APPLE_ID="you@example.com"
APPLE_PASSWORD="xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx"
APPLE_TEAM_ID="XXXXXXXXXX"

# Or App Store Connect API key instead of Apple ID (uncomment + fill):
# APPLE_API_KEY="XXXXXXXXXX"
# APPLE_API_ISSUER="xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx"
# APPLE_API_KEY_PATH="$HOME/AuthKey_XXXXXXXXXX.p8"
